OL,3,CThe wind down of SD TV, MW and LW
OL,4,Cservices
OL,6,FIt is safe to assume ITV, Channel 4
OL,7,Fand Channel 5 will turn off all
OL,8,Fduplicate SD satellite feeds of their
OL,9,Fmain channels in the near future too.
OL,10,FMore ITV 1 SD regions shut in January.
OL,12,FIf the departure of BBC services goes
OL,13,Fsmoothly, as will almost certainly be
OL,14,Fthe case, commercial channels
OL,15,Fcertainly should not hold back.
OL,17,FThe moral of the story is that those
OL,18,Fwho predict the imminent end of linear
OL,19,Ftelevision are yet again demonstrating
OL,20,Fthat they do not understand that
OL,21,Funiversal access is a vital principle
OL,22,Fof public service broadcasting.
OL,1,W~+$ hw1~{4~k4 ~shw1~sj7}         G3/8
