OL,3,CThe wind down of SD TV, MW and LW
OL,4,Cservices
OL,6,FI suspect Radio 4 LW and 5 Live MW
OL,7,Fbroadcasts have a few more years in
OL,8,Fthem ` simply to ensure virtually
OL,9,Fnobody is left disadvantaged. They
OL,10,Fwill finally close when equipment
OL,11,Fneeds replaced or when it is possible
OL,12,Fto say with confidence that virtually
OL,13,Fnobody is listening.
OL,15,FAll this contrasts with what now seems
OL,16,Fto be a stampede to turn off
OL,17,Fcommercial MW radio services.
OL,19,FIt emerged over the weekend that Bauer
OL,20,Fis to turn off several MW transmitters
OL,21,Fwithin weeks.
OL,1,W~+$ hw1~{4~k4 ~shw1~sj7}         G6/8
